  correct_answer = 'B',
  explanation = 'The phrase "all been born long ago" is used to emphasize the age and longevity of the trees.  This makes the trees seem ancient and venerable, which would be a sign of their importance in the passage. The passage states that "The speaker notes that the trees had "all been born long ago." This phrase suggests that the trees were alive before any…", which is the textual anchor for eliminating weaker choices. Choice B is correct because it aligns with that evidence: suggest that the trees are ancient and venerable.. Each incorrect option either contradicts a explicit detail, imports information not present in the text, or answers a different question than the one asked.',
